# Copy to `.env` for local dev:  copy .env.example .env
#
# =============================================================================
# Link the app to the SAME data as the web app (production database)
# =============================================================================
# The mobile app does NOT connect to MySQL/Postgres directly. It only talks to
# your Django backend over HTTPS. That backend is what uses your production DB.
#
# So: set EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL to the public base URL of your deployed API — the
# same host your web app uses (see web: VITE_API_URL in Zenotimeflow-frontend).
#
# Examples:
#   - If web calls https://zenotimeflow.com/api/...  → use origin:
#       EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://zenotimeflow.com
#   - If you use a dedicated API subdomain:
#       EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.zenotimeflow.com
#
# The app normalizes this to .../api (see src/lib/api-client.ts). Use HTTPS in production.
#
# EAS cloud builds: set the same variable for the build profile, e.g.
#   eas secret:create --scope project --name EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL --value https://your-domain.com
# or add "env": { "EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL": "https://..." } under the profile in eas.json
#
# =============================================================================
# Local development (backend on your PC)
# =============================================================================
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000
